          "text": "Working with Images"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Images can be embedded in your wiki pages to illustrate concepts and provide visual context."
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Image Best Practices"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": true,
          "items": [
            {"text": "Use descriptive alt text for accessibility"},
            {"text": "Keep image files reasonably sized for web"},
            {"text": "Use appropriate file formats (PNG for graphics, JPG for photos)"},
            {"text": "Provide captions to explain the image context"},
            {"text": "Ensure images are responsive on mobile devices"}
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Supported Formats"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": false,
          "items": [
            {"text": "PNG - Best for graphics and screenshots"},
            {"text": "JPG - Best for photographs"},
            {"text": "WebP - Modern format with better compression"},
            {"text": "SVG - Vector graphics, scalable"}
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
